name: The Cat Man - 1971
description: Harold, or as he called himself, "The Cat Man", came over while we were getting gas (27¢ per gallon!) to ask for a ride to Brownsville, Texas, about 30 miles away. He wanted to go live underneath the International Bridge that connects Brownsville to Matamoros, Mexico.  He had hitch hiked from Ohio, because he had heard that camping under that bridge was the best place to live out his days. After we gassed up, he climbed in the back and we took him there.  Original photo taken on Plus-X 35mm film with a Praktica FX2 camera.
